  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Ischemia reperfusion injury causes the release of free oxygen radicals. The selective
      alpha2-receptor agonist, dexmedetomidine, has an inhibitory effect on inflammatory responses
      during ischemic injury. The aim of this study is to evaluate the effect of dexmedetomidine on
      inflammatory responses during ischemia-reperfusion injury in skeletal muscle.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
